column1: •my first visit to greece was with my mother in 2004

column1: • it was also the season of the big box office hit “troy”

column2: i learned some deep truths about myself
column3: and also released much that no longer serves me.

column1: i am deeply saddened at the children that have been abused in the documentary of surviving r kelly.
i am also grateful and happy that we are evolving as a society where
we are fighting for justice for all.
i grew up in an environment where there was a lot of child abuse both
physically and sexually amongst family and friends.
i personally experience many attempts as a under age child by older men. be it friends of family or stranger trying to sexually abuse me.
i am happy and grateful that i had to strength to fight the men that
how you ask?! “i literally physically fought adult men off me with my fist!” 👊
maybe its because the only fight i saw between my parents was my mom holding my dad against the wall with all her strength and not backing down.
maybe it’s from my grandma that lives her life by listening to the music of her soul and marching her own drums. living her life in truth and strength.
maybe its because i was surrounded by a loving family that gave me unconditional love as i knew i was not alone. i know that i could always talk to them about everything.

column3: the husband tried to abuse me. i physically fought back
column4: one of my sister saw it and jumped

column1: we were 11 and 13 girls fighting a grown 40+ years old man!

column2: we were kicked out in the street with no where to go.

column1: as sad as this story may seem
i had my sister. i had love. i had support. i had god.
i was one of the lucky one that got away.
it is important that we see that these victims may have grown up
seeing their parents or have been brainwash to be “helpless” as girls.
the mental health effects of sexual assault and abuse has long term effect.
i am posting this so that yes
column2: men and women as this also happen the other way around get help!

column1: these people are sick and need help.
sharing your story is just the beginning…
it is important that we fix the problem at its core
column2: and not by simply putting a bandage on the wound.

column1: 83051;instagram;2019-01-09 22:35:22;FALSE;"i’ve thought about writing this countless times
column2: never quite mustering up the strength to do so.  but today
column3: i’m taking my power back from the person who took it 13 years ago.

column2: and only so much ‘kissed a boy.’ i was raped by one of the most ‘popular’ boys in school. he told me not to tell anyone

column1: i didn’t understand what had happened. my body hurt. i was sad and disgusted. i blamed myself. i have for years.
shoving it so deep into my brain that it caused other areas of my life to suffer. i stopped valuing myself
column3: my grades. i developed an eating disorder and i ruined relationships i was fortunate to have. i hurt so many people. i spiraled and i didn’t know why.

column1: i blamed myself for being in a bad situation
column2: for telling him later that it was ‘okay’. for not fighting harder
column3: for not saying ‘no’ louder. for not kicking and screaming my way out of that car and running home
column4: no matter how far away it was.  i blamed myself for giving up. on myself.

column1: i regret not speaking up. for being so afraid and so ashamed that i didn’t tell the two people who would’ve fought for me
column3: i hid it away and punished myself for another’s actions.

column1: i didn’t speak up and i put others at risk. but for every #metoo and #timesup that i’ve seen
column2: it sparked within me a sigh of relief that someone else was doing what i couldn’t do.

column4: and no matter what they mean to you. if you feel like something is wrong for you

column1: fight. kick. scream. run. run far away. and if you do give up
column3: be kind to yourself. pick yourself up and take a stand for you. because if you don’t
column4: it’ll eat at you in its own awful way.

column1: don’t ever give up on yourself
column2: fear and shame don’t belong here.";;en;#metoo

column1: 83055;instagram;2019-01-09 22:38:20;FALSE;"in october 2018 i ended a 4 year long abusive relationship. my life changed drastically in a 1000 ways. some negative. some positive. all for a reason. my new years resolution is to talk about it. i have been too scared
column2: embarrassed and forbidden to do that. i want to share my story and hear yours. i want to help others heal while also healing myself. i want to live my life freely and focus on the things that matter most with less distractions. be in the moment. time is precious. don’t waste it with the wrong people.

@anthony.tilotta just sent me this post and i want to cry because i finally learned there there is a name to what some family members did to me for years. gaslighting.

column2: i’m being called crazy for speaking out about what happened to me as a child. it’s being totally denied by the people who have the most to lose by accepting the truth.

column1: for years i was scared and doubted myself🤯 because of gaslighting. i felt insecure because every time my abusers abused me and i called them out on it they denied it. sometimes outright. other times they said the abuse was normal and that i was just being “too sensitive” and that i should “get over it”. “every family is messed up danielle. let it go”

well i’m not letting it go 😡and neither should you. if someone is gaslighting you know that this is just one form of abuse. you might be like me and have endured multiple types of abuse. but any abuse is intolerable 🙅🏼‍♀️it is not normal. so speak to a professional🗣 talk to someone who can help you. silence is what allows the abuse to continue 🤐and it needs to stop 🛑 now👇🏻#stoptheabuse #endthesilence #metoo";;en;#endthesilence

column2: i committed myself to building my new life. amidst my challenges and baggage
column3: starting kc makeup pushed me to live out my passion of making women more confident in their own skin. i introduced positive habits into my life such as exercising
column6: and removing toxic people from my space. basically
column7: me first. i had a lot of anger & resentment towards my parents but  now realize they did the best they could do and meant no harm
column8: they love me to bits & i know this. change was slow and there were a lot of setbacks
column9: but through persistence my life started to gain positive momentum. my makeup work started being featured in numerous magazines and a career highlight was doing @priyankachopra's makeup in 2013. after the #metoo event
column10: i achieved my biggest goal to date by confronting my abuser face to face after 33 years of silence. it turns out that this sick f*ck hadn’t just molested me but many others
column11: including few of my female cousins. at our meeting
column12: i did not hesitate to let him know that he is a criminal who deserves to spend the rest of his life in jail & that the damage he caused was unforgivable
column13: unacceptable & irreversible - he responded with denial. despite his response
column14: i walked away a free woman - i didn’t need his admittance or apology to know my truth. thankfully
column15: through my work in therapy i was able to repair my relationships with my immediate family and i had their unconditional support throughout
column16: which was a victory in and of itself. along my journey
column17: i have realized that you have to speak up for anyone to understand where you’re coming from
column18: but i acknowledge that it's not always easy to get to that point. for those who are looking for a safe space to begin their healing process

column21: with india holding the #1 position. the only way we can reverse these statistics is by supporting & educating one another. never give up on yourself & your dreams. in solidarity - kc. #metoo;;en;#MeToo

column1: 83311;instagram;2019-01-09 18:41:44;FALSE;i believe this is one of the most important things to remember when making important decisions your emotions and thoughts of what you want are the most important. throughout the legal process i continued to stay true to what i believed was best for myself and my mental and emotional state. before i started this instagram page i spoke out and shared my story on twitter. i had a lot of support but i also received a lot of negativity. people told me i was a lying and making this up just to get money. not many people know this but when i pressed charges i went through the isabella county prosecutors office
column2: i did not hire my own attorney. money was never an option. i made my own decision to press charges and continue with the case. throughout the case plea deals and offers were made none of which involved money. even if being paid was an option i would not have taken it. i made all of the decisions i made for me and thinking about the future. this man is in medical school studying to be a surgeon and i thought about what else he could be capable of given this platform. despite not getting the verdict that should’ve happened
column3: i believe everything happens for a reason and i have learned so much about myself and grown so much through my journey of healing. i did this for me. 🦋 | #growth #healing #caterpillartobutterfly #survivor #metoo #law;;en;#growth

column1: 83328;instagram;2019-01-09 18:48:29;FALSE;"dame dash finally opens up about aaliyah’s relationship with jay-z
dame dash is finally opening up about aaliyah and her relationship with jay-z…yup…aaliyah and jay actually kicked it a little bit prior to baby girl’s relationship with dame.
he sat down with hip hop motivation and revealed that his former best friend had a past relationship with the singer.

column2: but jay was going at her. he knew her before i did
column3: ” he said. “it was a situation where aaliyah was the type of girl that would give you a shot. she didn’t care what people thought. so she’ll date you and be your friend. but you might end up in the friend zone… you wasn’t gonna just hit that. at least that was my experience.” @rkelly @theresakelly2701 #projectwakeyoassup #music #soulmusic #rnb #artist #talmud #destiny #groove #vibe #hiphop #senator #instagood #producer #sports #king #entertainment #sex #musicindustry #actor #pedophile #lawyer #judge #culture #aaliyah #rkelly #survivingrkelly #molestation #metoo";;en;#ProjectWakeYoAssUp

column1: 83339;instagram;2019-01-09 16:33:55;FALSE;"i’ve had three fathers in my life…

column2: one abused me and one made my worst nightmare come true. so to say i have #daddyissues is an understatement.

column1: i spent a lot of years looking at men through a lens based on my past. i had relationship issues
column2: abandonment fears and a belief that men were not to be trusted. but slowly i started realizing
column3: i can’t judge half of the worlds population based upon the actions of 3 people.  we create our own “truths” based upon our experiences but that doesn’t necessarily make them true.

column1: i still find myself going back to those “made up truths” on occasion and i don’t know if they will ever completely go away.  but now i can recognize them and know they aren’t truth and be intentional on working through the feelings.  i’m a constant work in progress.

no matter your past.  no matter the situation that may have hardened your heart or created your own personal “truth”…don’t let those bad experiences in your life determine how you look at life.  there is so much you may be missing out on.";;en;#daddyissues;;;;;0;;dionnahickox;D I O N N A   H I C K O X;;0;False;28;0;0;157;https://instagram.fyvr3-1.fna.fbcdn.net/vp/c4b7e2a0add2f14b891c18bc4944ab2c/5D0DD4E6/t51.2885-15/e35/49802190_2272829072997104_7084631139696263888_n.jpg?_nc_ht=instagram.fyvr3-1.fna.fbcdn.net;0;FALSE;FALSE;FALSE;english;"i’ve had three fathers in my life…

column1: 83342;instagram;2019-01-09 18:05:17;FALSE;"i don’t spend a lot time on single joint isolation exercises. especially when considering the general population. however
column2: when programming a training session. i will often pair exercises. one single joint exercise with a multi joint exercise. i refer to it as an (a) movement and a (b) movement. this is different from what many coaches may title a “complex”.🏋🏽‍♀️
one of our major challenges is creating appropriate levels of exercise stress. sometimes that means taking your foot off the gas. but also
column3: we are charged with maximizing the training session with respect to ⏰time. a back squat is a very physically demanding exercise. i don’t have enough time in a 45min session to allow the client to completely recovery from a set of back squats. instead
column4: i will pair an elbow extension with a back squat
column5: for example. this gives the client an opportunity to recover from the intensity of the back squat. while providing some lower intensity single joint exercise stress. i consider single joint exercises auxiliaries. in my program
column6: they are only used to support and assist the advancement of our big multi joint movements. at the most
column7: they only account for about 1/3 of an individual training session. regardless of the type of resistance used.🏋🏽‍♀️ #eitherquitorcommit #ubetterlovethislife #bestinatlanta";;en;#eitherquitorcommit

column1: 83552;instagram;2019-01-09 16:08:51;FALSE;"thank you @fatimata25 fatima ishiaku for the courage to speak up.

fatima is a #sexualviolence survivor who recalls being raped daily by her step father from age 7 to 14. do you know all the while she thought that was her biological father? and that her mother never believed what she was going through?
she has lost her engagement twice
column2: been bullied and shamed by confidants
column3: attempted suicide and stigmatized because she shared her story.

column1: fast forward to today she can proudly say she is a survivor but she is concerned about those still not able to break the silence culture. she shares her story in her soon to be published book.
awlo will be helping fatima touch more lives
column2: and create a sensitization; for more women to speak up
column3: find the courage to share their story and let this be their stepping stone and not a label. this is fatima's message.

column1: i went out to dc to shoot a video this past weekend. as soon as the doors locked in the lyft to head out the morning of i felt the panic attack set in.
i didn't have an issue with the song or anybody shooting the vid either
column2: but the uneasiness continued when i got there...

column1: the day went on. shit got heavier. i still didn't put my finger on what was up until about 3 or 4. my mind shuts out certain portions of my past unless i'm triggered & that day was one of those places inside.

to avoid a full novel here that day over the weekend was the anniversary of being raped. the day it happened i left my body and my mind & found comfort in the fact that there was protection used. at least disease or pregnancy wouldn't be worries on my mind.

in traumatic moments sometimes your mind latches onto smth it can control to avoid what's happening that it can't. a silver lining of sorts i guess you can say. i still heard everything tho. i heard the door lock. most of my triggers are audible things as a result.
that day i repress so deep down. that am with him driving me in a locked lyft set me off in a totally safe space. whether it's #metoo #cosby #rkelly or any other movement that pulls your attention
column2: know that trauma follows you everywhere you go.

column1: you just have to heal through best you can. you do what you have to in order to get thru. you soak up all the love & understanding you can on the smoother days & you pull from em when the waves get rough.
logical acknowledgement is a must. don't let how you feel about the politics take energy away from just doing better for our future generations.

a friend has a cabin in the woods i went to decompress in. everything down to the movies i watched felt like signs that everything is still going to be ok. another year past & all in all i'm still good.
i had to acknowledge what was being triggered & why. i had to give it its moment
column2: but i didn't have to give it more life. there are always gonna be ups & downs. filter em in your life the healthiest way you know how. reach out if u need to. easier said than done sometimes
column3: lord don't i know it. hang in there tho. ur gonna get thru. #wellnesswednesday ✊";;en;#MeToo

column1: 83569;instagram;2019-01-09 16:20:13;FALSE;"this is reality.  someone who is abused may abuse others. incest is when siblings engage in sexual activity with each other.  please understand that this is an abuse construct.  it’s not natural or normal
column2: but a manifestation of inappropriate behavior being repeated within the family due to one person being targeted by rapedor molestation.  that person may then abuse  family members of that family. once the abuse begins some may repeat it and some may not.

column1: my question to you is this. after hearing the r. kelly stories
column2: after watching this clip. what steps will you take to help your children understand inappropriate sexual touch?  what tools does your child have to tell you they have been touched? what system does your school or church have?

column1: let me advise you that it is well documented that individuals who have suffered abuse find it extremely difficult to tell.

column2: i want to offer a great solution. it my book titled “hurt people help people”. you see i was the victim of child molestation
column3: incest and rape.  i was blessed to tell when i was very young. although the abuse had happened for years
column4: i’m glad i found the courage to speak up and the abuse stopped.

column1: but i realized one thing as i grew up.  i ran into countless others who were being abused. friends
column4: students and kids i was going to church with.  i literally became an advocate as a teen.  confronting abusers
column5: helping others tell their parents and being the source of information and comfort.

column1: i have not stopped. i confronted older guys in the community and told them they were child molesters and rapists and they should stay away from us young girls. just like r. kelly they would sit near the school or near the areas we hung out at to take advantage of us as kids.
i do not want the coach
column3: the youth pastor or anyone for that matter to lead your child down a destructive path. please
column4: purchase the book!  i wish i could donate them
column5: but i can’t. you can buy as many as you like and distribute them to family
column7: churches or other organizations. let’s heal from the inside out.

column1: 83636;instagram;2019-01-09 15:08:36;FALSE;"former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel
column2: but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

column1: in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23
column2: flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia
column3: and kushner spoke with kim darroch
column4: the british ambassador to the united states
column5: according to diplomats familiar with the conversations
column6: who spoke on condition of anonymity.

column1: the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump
column2: who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric
column3: took office on jan. 20. it failed
column4: with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

column1: the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move
column2: egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution
column3: prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

column1: a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a ""high level"" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.
according to court documents made public on friday
column2: a member of trump's presidential transition team
column3: later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner
column4: told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments
column6: to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

column1: 83644;instagram;2019-01-09 15:13:18;FALSE;"an interesting article about the cost of addiction to families and the person in pain.

financial stress is one of the most important factors that led me to treatment because i had accumulated debt from helping my brother who was injured during his community service for his dui. the debt really really stressed me out and my own drinking increased as my stress increased until i missed an important presentation.
i realized that i was going to be in this cycle of overdrinking
column2: overeating and overspending for the rest of my life if i didn't stop now. since i could not stop drinking despite putting all my effort into it i took the bold move to get help before i lost everything.

column1: when i went to treatment i was 20k in credit card debt but randomly received an old bonus payout for the insurance deductible right before i made the decision to get help. this was truly a gift from the universe and allowed me to pay cash for that part of the treatment and my insurance benefits covered the rest.
when i got home i enrolled in @daveramsey financial peace university and attended for 9 weeks in the summer of 2017. i cancelled all my travel plans and committed to financial freedom and soberity.

column2: my remaining car balance and all my medical expenses before i hit one year sober but i didn't understand how addictive and powerful credit cards are so i relapsed back into it in june of 2018.

column1: i recommited to financial freedom and on january 2nd of this year (last week) i was able to get myself out of credit card debt for the second time and will never go back. i have felt such a wonderful sense of peace and calm and love using #daveramsey plan 💓

financial habits are incredibly difficult to change and improve but it is possible with help and education from people who have been through it. the #daveramsey podcast helped me so much in meeting this goal! my goal was to be healthy and wealthy... for me this meant sober and debt free and it's absolutely wonderful

column1: 83647;instagram;2019-01-09 15:13:47;FALSE;"have you ever felt naked in a public place? as if the eyes of a hundred men were shedding you of your dignity? we were standing by the roadside yesterday
column2: waiting for our cab in broad daylight
column3: when we saw a sad story unfold. a group of three women walked past us. one of them raised her arms to fix the back of her kurta
column4: which raised the shawl that she had carefully draped around her. so
column6: you could see the shape of her breasts a bit more clearly. no cleavage
column9: no flimsy cloth. just the shape. this caught the eye of a lecherous middle-aged man. he ogled
column10: he pointed her out to his friend
column11: he made a comment about ’tapping that’
column12: made a slurping gesture with his tongue
column13: did not take his eyes off her even as she walked away in the traffic
column14: and then followed her on his bike for a short distance before riding away. all because she was fixing her kurta
column16: that was an invitation. this man probably has a wife
column18: and sisters. and he probably leches at them too. most cases of sexual assault happen behind the closed doors of a household. and while #metoo was a big step that motivated women to call out such men
column19: there are many women who do not speak up because these men are a part of their families. if you are facing something similar at home
column23: speak up. speak to an elder in your family who can help you out. and if you see someone else in your family being assaulted
column24: don’t ignore it. let them know that you will stand by them if they want to raise their voice. because no one should feel unsafe in their own homes. do you have any more tips on how to deal with a situation like this? tell us! it matters. period. 📷 @milanzrnic

column1: 83767;instagram;2019-01-09 13:33:03;FALSE;"2018 has been a roller coaster ride for the oppressed and the oppressor
column2: for the helpless and the powerful and for the campaigners and the bashers. from marital rape to homosexuality to #metoo we have come a long way.

column1: and the much needed online campaign against sexual harassers was the greatest highlight of the year!
what is now very popularly promoted and also sometimes misused is the #metoo movement. though this movement gained global popularity in the last one year
column2: the roots of this movement were sowed long ago in the early 2000s when tarana burke
column3: an african- american civil rights social activist first used this phrase and who was herself a victim of such assault. talking about its spread in india
column4: it received massive attention when tanushree dutta
column5: a bollywood celebrity accused nana patekar of his inappropriate behaviour during the shoot of a film. since then
column6: many personalities from different industries including tv actor alok nath
column7: comedian utsav chakraborty and politician mj akbar have been accused by women for harassing them sexually. this movement needs to be considered as an important step towards a safer society and workplaces.

column1: considering this matter of utmost importance
column2: companies have been asked to set up internal committees that employees can comfortably use to file any such case. companies have also taken steps to avoid such cases by clearly stating different acts of sexual harassment
column3: by employing more females to the internal complaints committee and encouraging employees to come up when such cases happen
column4: by conducting a detailed background verification of new employees. these steps can lead us to a safer society and a better workplace.

column1: indian womyn did not come to play in 2019. and thank god(dess) for that! our sacred blood makes us holy. the end.
vermillion goddess red tent stands in proud solidarity with our kerala sisters!
5.5 million womyn forming a human chain spanning 385 miles. what a divine feminine way to set a precedent! “some hindus believe that menstruation is unclean
column2: and that women should be excluded from daily activities and live in isolation when they have their periods. and some hindu temples bar women from entry while they are on their periods under the belief that their mere presence could “defile” the religious space. the sabarimala temple took this patriarchal and discriminatory practice even further by barring entry by women of menstruating age altogether.
women standing up for their bodies and their rights threatens and intimidates many people and institutions everywhere. here in the united states
column3: we must stand in solidarity with the women’s resistance in kerala. as women around the united states march for our rights later this month
column4: let us remember and express our support of the women’s wall in kerala. as we build the #metoo movement in the united states
column5: let us also uplift the brave stories of indian women who are speaking up.”";en;#Repost

column1: 83787;instagram;2019-01-09 12:38:38;FALSE;"we have opened  up our first freedom event of the year to men and professionals who deal with dv. as a ministry we have been supporting women empowering them and helping them to deal with the after effects of all forms of abuse.
we are so tierd of hearing of more women being killed in their homes and have decided to extend the work.
we have decided to open up freedom and we will be looking to have freedom for men too.
come and join us on 26 january 2019 from 11am to 3pm. we will have the opportunity to speak share and learn together as a community.
if you provide services to victims of domestic abuse or run perpetrator programmes please come and showcase the work you are doing and tell people so they can access your services.

column1: exhibition highlight! sideshow by @leandraurrutia and @hfwetzel is an interactive installation piece with magic boxes - a deceptive puzzle that can be opened from two directions
column2: revealing the contents of only one side at a time. want to know what’s in the other box? come to the exhibit & find out. on view now with a reception on jan. 25!

column1: artists' statement: ""women's voices and standpoints continue to be viewed as sideshow material. instead of being taken seriously
column2: the agency of women with the courage to expose the character flaws and misdeeds of powerful men has been reduced to fodder that bemuses and entertains. large bank accounts work their magic so that the public finds it hard to discern truth from lies
column3: muddying the waters when proof of dishonesty and nefarious acts surface. trickery becomes unavoidable when reality does not align with the beliefs and positions of the despicable."" #metoo #mcaexhibition #enough #installationart";en;#Repost

column1: i got so many supportive dms from people who have known me for a long time + they know i have been through a lot +  the injustice so many lgbt+ youth at my old school because they reached out for help yet all they heard was "" we'll handle it ""  but i'm dealing with a lot right now because yangs birthday is coming up soon + everything is a mess right now and its always a hard time for me. because i feel if i pretended to be straight and cis that they wouldn't have done that to him.

when i think of him i just feel so many dark feelings and i'm just hurting a lot because i miss him still. i'm just a mess right now honestly i'm doing my best.i might delete this later i'm not sure. i just needed to let it out because right now it feels like i'm drowning.

if you would like to hear stories from some of the other lgbt+ youth who went to my school.. and just the area we lived in ill ask if i can share their stories because i had it real  bad but some had it worse mostly the lesbians and anyone under the trans spectrum. i feel real bad for the bis and polys who were pressured into dating those of the opposite gender because they basically had to if they didn't wanna get beat up. ~ witchy

column1: 83886;instagram;2019-01-09 11:24:44;FALSE;take a moment to read my thoughts: i boycotted r. kelleys music in 2002 when i saw the video ~ i know it was him. clearly.  i wasn’t comfortable talking about it because the world i lived in .... everyone thought it was a joke
column2: and they made me feel ike i was too earnest. i saw the bbc documentary
column3: i read the buzz feed and new yorker articles ... as a #survivor and a black woman in the music industry
column4: i just broke down sobbing when i saw the video. i sobbed
column5: because it was a graphic illustration
column6: that i lived in a world that didnt value people like me. and i had to learn to take care of myself in the face of a society and industry that doesn’t love me. i learned that i had to wear the crown of my ancestors and hold my own head up. and its been hard. but i do it because i believe in my mission ~ i don’t need to sing about the fight
column7: my mission is to administer to the people in the fight. humanity makes me sad all the time ~ the things were going thru ... but also today
column9: that we as a group are now #muterkelly ~ but
column10: i wont be satisfied until every #survivor know
column11: that “everyone of us is worthy” and when ever someone treats us as less
column13: ... and while the wound is not our doing
column14: it is our responsibility ~ we have to heal ourselves.  that healing can take on so much more momentum
column15: when the world around us is healing too.... so i feel good today knowing that we as a collective are waking up even more
column16: to the ways that the world / the music industry / the society / the culture ~ harm our women and girls.  and! i feel good today knowing that these growing pains are about growth. we are all! worthy and significant and we matter! because we exist!  may we keep waking up to that fact. it is a fact! everyone of us is #worthy #worthy #worthy #worthy #worthy #worthy #survivingrkelly #iamlight #muterkelly #survivingrkelly #rkelly #blackgirlsmatter #metoo;;en;#survivor

hotelové pokoje na různých patrech . vyvarujte se individuálních jednání . muži po celé wall street přijímají kontroverzní strategie pro éru uvádí světoznámá agentura bloomberg . na základě rozhovorů více než 30 vedoucími pracovníky právnických firem , investičních společností či bank agentura bloomberg prý zjistila , že jsou tito lidé hnutím vyděšeni . muži po celých spojených státech v práci kontrolují své chování , aby nebyli náhodou osočeni ze sexuálního obtěžování . touto šílenou politickou korektností budou nakonec postiženy ženy . muži se nimi raději nebudou bavit , nepozvou je na skleničku . bude pomalu trestné navázat jakýkoli vztah se ženou . je výsledek zrůdné politiky genderu , která povede k segregaci pohlaví , osamělosti , atomizaci společnosti , frustraci také smutku některých mužů žen… takové „ západní “ výdobytky tady nechceme . zatímco imigranti pomalu beztrestně mnohdy hromadně znásilňují někdy vraždí ženy dívky , slušní muži budou pomalu trestně stíháni za , column1: 83993;instagram;2019-01-09 08:34:56;FALSE;"amesha monique (@ameshamonique_photography ) is our woman of the week and our #wcw. she is a very important woman of so cal
column2: as she was the photographer for the women of so cal brunch in october. 📸

column1: she did an amazing job caputuring the event
column2: the women who attended and the food everyone loved so much (thanks again @breakfastbarlb ). she captured such wonderful memories. her energy was peaceful and her presence was commanding. we met through a mutual friend on facebook (@rednimz) and although we had never met in person
column3: it felt as if we were long lost friends.

column1: amesha is a photogapher that loves to caputure beauty in all its forms. her focus is on empowering black woman through showcasing them as a standard of beauty. while she began taking photos years ago
column2: she has become laser focused on her passion in the past three years.

column1: she has a unique view of the world not only as a black woman — but through through her journey with an eye condition that required a corneal transplant. her eye condition is what has given her an appreciation for sight and beauty of all kinds.
amesha is the perfect example of things in our lives that may have been intended to hold us back and are actually gifts and allow us to feel deep gratitude for what we have been provided.

column2: she plans to do a few shoots involving plus size woman and seemingly ""unconventional"" beauties. whose interested!? dm her!

column1: be on the lookout for this fabulous photographer! she has a wonderful gift and i look forward to what she has in store for this year ✨
